-- Bank Asya shares up 8 percent after resumption of trade 
-- By Seda Sezer
-- Thu Sep 18, 2014 07:51AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Sept 18 (Reuters) - Shares in Turkey's Bank Asya <ASYAB.IS>, an Islamic finance institution, rose 7.8 percent on Thursday afternoon as trade resumed following a brief suspension due to volatility in the price.

The shares initally tumbled 11 percent at the opening on Thursday but then rebounded sharply to gain 11 percent before being suspension.